recommandationVideos.Title: Sparks! Nicole Yunger Halpern
recommandationVideos.Description: Nicole Yunger Halpern is a theoretical physicist at the Joint Center for Quantum Information and Computer Science at the University of Maryland. Nicole reenvisions the science of energy, developed during the 1800s, for the 21st century, using the mathematical tools of quantum computing. She has dubbed this research 람uantum steampunk, after the steampunk genre of art and literature that juxtaposes Victorian settings with futuristic technologies. The field뗩 insights and aesthetic form the subject of her book for the general public, Quantum Steampunk: The Physics of Yesterday뗩 Tomorrow. The book received the PROSE Award for Popular Science and Mathematics from the Association of American Publishers.  Nicole earned her PhD at Caltech, winning the international Ilya Prigogine Prize for an energy-science thesis. She won the International Quantum Technology Emerging Researcher Award from Britain뗩 Institute of Physics as a postdoctoral fellow at Harvard. In 2023, Nicole received the U.S. ASPIRE Prize for young scientists.  Nicole has written over 100 articles for the blog Quantum Frontiers and suspects that a copy of her is a novelist in some parallel universe. You can follow her on Twitter @nicoleyh11.

Olen ymm칛rt칛nyt, ett칛 se on opposition l칛칛ke hyvinvointialueiden, kuntien ja kaikkien muidenkin ongelmien ratkomiseen, mutta se ei my칬sk칛칛n n칛y n칛iss칛 teid칛n vaihtoehtobudjeteissanne, ett칛 annetaan aina lis칛칛 rahaa n칛iden ongelmien ratkomiseen. Se kyll칛 nimenomaan lis칛칛 ty칬llisyytt칛. [V칛lihuutoja vasemmalta  Niina Malm: Mites se ty칬ntekij칬iden n칛k칬kulma?] 

Sitten seuraavaksi t칛h칛n hallituksen nelj칛n miljardin investointiohjelmaan, joka ei siis suinkaan k칛sit칛 ainoastaan Turun tunnin junaa, kuten t칛칛ll칛 annetaan ymm칛rt칛칛, vaan nelj칛n miljardin investointiohjelman koko Suomeen. Sen lis칛ksi on viel칛 muita toimia. N칛m칛h칛n kustannetaan myym칛ll칛 valtion omaisuutta, eli ainoastaan peruuttamalla n칛ist칛 toimista ei saada yht칛칛n valtiontaloutta parempaan kuntoon. [Antti Kurvinen: Onko Peltokangas samaa mielt칛?]

T칛ll칛kin viikolla ja viime viikolla on paljon puhuttu hyvinvointialueiden vakavista alij칛칛mist칛 ja siit칛, kuinka vaikea siell칛 on l칬yt칛칛 erilaisia tehostamiskeinoja. Sosiaalidemokraateille: Hallitus ei puhu ty칬st칛 abstraktina asiana tai ajattele, ett칛 ty칬paikat syntyv칛t vain julkiselle sektorille, vaan me huolehdimme siit칛, ett칛 ne ovat konkreettisia, niit칛 syntyy yksityiselle sektorille. recommandationVideos.Title: Putin Visits Kaliningrad Day After T칲rkiye Approves Sweden's NATO Bid
recommandationVideos.Description:
Turkiye's President Erdogan has signed off on Sweden's request to join NATO after the Turkish parliament's ratification of the bid earlier this week. The move comes 20 months after the Scandinavian country first applied to join the alliance in response to Russia's attack on Ukraine. And the reaction has been swift, especially in Washington. The White House sent a letter to top lawmakers, urging Congress to approve a long delayed F-16 fighter jet deal to Turkiye.

Ankara has been trying to purchase 40 upgraded F-16s and dozens of modernization kits from Washington since 2021, but US lawmakers insisted they would only consider the sale once Turkiye approves Sweden's NATO accession. Both Sweden and Finland abandoned their decades of neutrality to join the alliance, citing Russia's aggression against Ukraine. Moscow, which criticized Finland's formal entry into NATO last year, called Ankara's approval of Sweden's bid a 'sovereign decision'. With Turkiye's greenlight, Hungary remains the last hurdle to Sweden joining the alliance.

Etenemist칛 jatkettiin 23. elokuuta Koivuselk칛칛n ja silet칛 edelleen Uomaan kyl칛칛n. Elokuun lopussa 1941 rykmentti ylitti vanhan rajan K칛sn칛sel칛n ja Kolatsel칛n v칛liss칛. L칛hteen칛 t칛ll칛 videolla olen k칛ytt칛nyt sotap칛iv칛kirjoja ja kolmea 2010-luvulla tekemi칛ni sotakirjoja. Kirjojen tekemisen taustalla oli is칛ni ja h칛nen nelj칛 velje칛, jotka palvelivat koko sodan ajan Jalkav칛kirykementti yhdeks칛n eri pataljoonissa.
